Reasoning: The paper deals with natural language inference and the ability of NLP models to capture semantic concepts related to tense and aspect. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) sub-category. Additionally, the paper proposes a novel entailment dataset and analyses the ability of NLP models to perform inference on temporal predications, which suggests that it could also belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the encoding of morphosyntactic information, which suggests that it could belong to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with reasoning with semantic properties, which suggests that it could also belong to the Symbolic Computation (cs.SD) sub-category.
